article.headline: Sacramento State 80, Cal Poly 59
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Freshman Loren Leath had 23 points, including five 3-pointers, to lead Sacramento State over Cal Poly 80-59 Tuesday night. Jason Harris added 16 points, five rebounds, and three assists for the Hornets (8-4), who are 4-0 at home. Derek Stockalper had 20 points and seven rebounds for the Mustangs (2-6), who still lead the all-time series 25-13. Trailing 8-7, Leath and Clark Woods came off the bench to hit two 3-pointers each to ignite an 18-2 run for Sacramento State. The Hornets led 40-31 at halftime. Cal Poly got within four points early in the second half, but Sacramento State was able to preserve the lead the rest of the way.
